[[File:Maspiro October 9 victims.jpg|thumb|right|Victims of the 9 October riots.]]
Late into the evening of October 9, during a protest that was held in [[Maspiro television building|Maspiro]] <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-15235212 |title=BBC News - Cairo clashes leave 24 dead after Coptic church protest |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref>, peaceful Egyptian protesters, calling for the dissolution the Supreme Council of the Armed Forces, the resignation of its chairman, Field Marshal Mohamed Tantawi, and the dismissal of the governor of Aswan province, [[Maspero demonstrations|were attacked]] by military police. At least 25 people<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/10/10/world/meast/egypt-protest-clashes/index.html?hpt=wo_c2 |title=Death toll rises in Egypt Christian clashes as tension continues - CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref> were killed and more than 200 wounded. The protest began due to an attack on a [[Coptic Orthodox Church of Alexandria|Coptic Christian]] church in Merinab village in [[Aswan]] on September 30. <ref name="alarabiya1">{{cite web|author=<!--[if IE 6]> <![endif]--> |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/articles/2011/10/09/170992.html |title=At least 36 dead in clashes between Copts and Egyptian security forces |publisher=English.alarabiya.net |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref> Aswan governor '''Mustafa al-Seyyed''' said that Copts had built the church without having the proper permits. <ref name="alarabiya1"/>. The October 9 attack was committed by both the Egyptian police force and military police<ref name="arabawy1">{{cite web|url=http://www.arabawy.org/2011/10/09/army-and-police-massacre-protesters-at-maspero/ |title=Army and police massacre protesters at Maspero Â« 3arabawy |publisher=Arabawy.org |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref> using live ammunition,<ref>{{cite web|last=Siddique |first=Haroon |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/middle-east-live/2011/oct/10/egypt-libya-middle-east-unrest-live?CMP=NECNETTXT8187 |title=Egypt, Libya and Middle East unrest - live updates | World news | guardian.co.uk |publisher=Guardian |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref> vehicles to run over protesters<ref>{{cite web|author=Reuters October 10, 2011 |url=http://www.montrealgazette.com/news/Church+clash+turns+deadly+Cairo/5526557/story.html |title=Church clash turns deadly in Cairo |publisher=Montrealgazette.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-10}}</ref> and extensive rounds of tear gas were fired.<ref name="arabawy1"/>
